INSERT INTO `Blog` VALUES (1,'1681341990','Creating this site','<p>This is the first post on this blog, so I thought the best idea was to write something about the website which you are currently using. This site is written in PHP 8.2, which I know many people hate PHP. I used PHP because I already knew some PHP from when I was at college.</p>\r\n<p>Personally I actually quite like PHP, I think it allows for very quick development, as very little is needed to be able to run a PHP site, all you need is xampp or a cheap server (like this one). I also know of PHPs flaws, i.e its security issues, which since the last time I used it seem to have gotten much easier to patch up (though I was never taught to a high level at college). Any feedback on this site is welcomed, other than aesthetics as I am currently wanted to figure that out myself, but if there is anything you think I should add or change in some way go ahead and tell me either by email baileydawson@baileydawson.uk or used the contact form.</p>\r\n<p>Hopefully in future I will think of some more interesting things to talk about</p>'),(7,'1681587939','Fortran, why I learnt it','I learnt Fortran because I wanted to get a better understanding of lower level computing.<br> You may say why didn\'t you learn assembly then, that is much lower level. I think Fortran is a low enough level that there is no point learning below that for the vast majority of people. Fortran works in a very similar way to assembly, like you need to pre create all variables before anything is done.<br>Its restrictions can also teach a lot about using less RAM. I was taught to code in a world where most computers have at least 4gb of RAM, but this isn\'t always the case. An example of this comes from my work, where I had to develop a full application to run on a machine that only has 2gb of RAM, this application had to load images all sorts while been open at the same time as the main application on the machine. I did in the end manage to limit the RAM usage enough to get it to work but it does run close to the line. I think now having learnt Fortran I would be able to create that same application again while using a lot less RAM.<br>I don\'t think everyone should learn Fortran though, its a every old and very hard language to use, and rather useless in the modern day. I think you should only learn it if you really want to learn how to use as little memory as possible.<br>I will post another blog about learning a higher level language, that been PHP (which this site is written in).');
